<topic id="preferences-editor-pages">
  <title>Edit modes Preferences</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Configure the Application<indexterm>Editor
              preferences<indexterm>pages</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> lets you configure which <xref keyref="chapter_edit-modes">edit
        mode</xref> a file is opened in the first time it is opened. This setting only affects the
      first time a file is opened. The current editing mode of each file is saved when the file is
      closed and restored the next time it is opened. To configure the <uicontrol>Edit
        modes</uicontrol> options, <ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/> and go
      to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Edit modes</uicontrol>
      </menucascade> .</p>
    <p product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse">If <uicontrol>Allow Document Type
        specific edit mode setting to override the general mode setting</uicontrol> is selected, the
      initial edit mode setting set in the <xref
        href="the-document-type-dialog.dita#the-document-type-dialog"><uicontrol>Document
          Type</uicontrol> configuration dialog box</xref> overrides the general edit mode setting
      from the table below.</p>
    <p>The initial edit mode can be one of the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><xref keyref="mode_text"><uicontrol>Text</uicontrol></xref></li>
      <li product="author authorEclipse editor editorEclipse"><xref keyref="mode_author"
            ><uicontrol>Author</uicontrol></xref></li>
      <li><xref keyref="mode_grid"><uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol></xref></li>
      <li><uicontrol>Design</uicontrol> (available only for the W3C XML Schema editor).</li>
    </ul>
